      • getOracleProductVersion

        public static java.lang.String getOracleProductVersion(Oracle oracle)
                                                throws java.sql.SQLException
        Returns the real product version of Oracle database, not the main release version. For 12c databases and older the JDBC method getDatabaseProductVersion of DatabaseMetadata class returns the banner value like Oracle Database 12c Enterprise Edition Release 12.1.0.2.0 - 64bit Production which contains the proper index. For 18c and beyond (V$VERSION seems to have changed), the banner value has the major Release number, but not the index like 19.3.x.x.x. For example: Oracle Database 18c Enterprise Edition Release 18.0.0.0.0 - Production and the product version is on banner full column of V$VERSION like: Oracle Database 18c Enterprise Edition Release 18.0.0.0.0 - Production Version 18.3.0.0.0 For 18c and beyond the JDBC method getDatabaseProductVersion of DatabaseMetadata class returns the banner full value
        Parameters:
        oracle -
        Returns:
        for databases 10c, 11c, and 12c will return the original value from JDBC DatabaseMetadata class method: Oracle Database 12c Enterprise Edition Release 12.1.0.2.0 - 64bit Production for 18c and beyond will return a string with the version number, for example 'Oracle Database Version 18.3.0.0.0'
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException

      • migrateApplicationTableIndex

        public static void migrateApplicationTableIndex(Oracle oracle,
                                                GraphOracleSem graph,
                                                int dop)
                                         throws java.sql.SQLException
        This method drops the old, default application table index name with a suffix "_triple_idx" and create a new application table index name with a shortened suffix "_idx"
        Parameters:
        oracle - maitains the connection to an Oracle database.
        graph - the GraphOracleSem object whose application table index name is to be migrated.
        dop - - degree of parallelism to be used for rebuilding the index.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException

      • removeDuplicates

        public static void removeDuplicates(Oracle oracle,
                                    java.lang.String model,
                                    boolean rebuildAppTabIndex)
                             throws java.sql.SQLException
        Remove duplicates from the application table of a given model. Please refer to user manual for details of SEM_APIS.REMOVE_DUPLICATES. NOTE that this API only works with database 11.2.0.1 and newer.
        Parameters:
        oracle - - database connection object. If it is NULL, then this method becomes a no-op.
        model - - name of the semantic model in Oracle database.
        rebuildAppTabIndex - - if set to true, then application table index will be dropped and rebuilt.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException
